steps.description:
Each box should be the size that holds 24 cans of beer. Make sure the boxes are dry and in good shape. Use the same brand for a more professional look or different brands if you want to showcase multiple kinds of beer. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f8/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be careful not to cut or rip the cardboard. This will ruin the box. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Once the boxes are unfolded, face the printed side of the box downwards towards the floor or tabletop. The brown cardboard from the inside of the box should face upward. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8a/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8a/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Flatten any lumps or uneven sections. This can be done with your hand or a hard, flat object like a book or ruler. The flatter you can make the empty beer boxes, the better your top hat will look. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fb/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fb/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remove the piece and set it aside. Use a compass to measure three inches out from the outside of the circle and draw another larger circle all the way around. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut out the larger circle from the edge of the box. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f3/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f3/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut out the inner circle from the inside so that you are left with a full ring. This will be the brim of your top hat. Set it aside with the top of your hat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lay the string out flat along the edge of the box. Mark on the box where the measured string ends. It is important that the length is the same as the length of the string you measured around your head. Measure at least four inches in from the edge and draw a straight line parallel to the edge. You can make it larger than four inches if you would like a taller top hat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a7/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a7/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut along the line so that you have a four-inch wide strip. Set this piece aside with the top and brim of the hat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ab/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ab/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The brown cardboard side should be facing up. Place the cylinder with the edges folded inwards on top of the top piece and adjust so that the edges all line up to the shape of the top piece. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/86/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use clear packing tape on the brown cardboard side along the inside of the cylinder to secure it to the top piece. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1e/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1e/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take the brim of the hat and align it with the shape of the top. Slide the brim all the way down the cylinder so that it sits on the bottom edge that is folded out. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use clear packing tape on the bottom cardboard side to secure the brim to the cylinder all the way around. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Beer-Box-Top-Hat-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
